message:
feat: Add fuzzy search for subject autocomplete and ChatGPT starter messages

- Added fuzzy matching (partial and token sort) to improve subject autocomplete during search.
- Prioritized matches: Top 10 > Same Major > Others.
- Integrated ChatGPT to generate personalized 2–3 line starter messages introducing user's name.
- Starter messages are saved into the chat_messages table and support regeneration through Socket.IO.

Note: Refactored Aryaa's search function into a separate search.py file for modularity.

[IMP] mail: add button to generate a mail with ChatGPT

Currently, the user can use ChatGPT to generate text inside the Odoo
editor using the /chatgpt command. Most users don't know that the command
exists. To showcase the feature, we will add a button to the mail composer
modal footer that will open a ChatGPT prompt dialog. The user will then
be able to type a prompt and insert a ChatGPT response to the mail body.

message:
Political Analysis Excel Files

I used ChatGPT to generate all of this data, and then I used MySQL to create the voter_data schema and tables within it. I used ChatGPT to act as a mentor/manager in a political organization to ask me questions in order to perform the exploratory data analysis of this fictional data. I did run into some issues with the data, as the "random" generation of the data by ChatGPT allowed for a more even distribution than a realistic dataset of voters, events, and outreach.
